  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to predict absolute hemolysis levels for centrifugal blood pump configurations under ventricular assist device operating conditions. The CFD hemolysis model targets the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry and was exercised across a range of VAD flow rates and rotational speeds representative of chronic implant use. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed over key rheological and geometric input parameters. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors were reviewed; seven were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps at Model Risk Level 5. The assessment team concluded that, for the intended clinical research application, the achieved credibility levels satisfy the thresholds established by the review panel under the Minimal profile declaration. No structured Context of Use object is registered in this package; the intended-use scope is conveyed solely through the narrative above.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-benchmark-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-hemolysis-experimental-dataset"
  ],
